(b) Carboxylic acid molecule has higher extent of H -bonding than alcohol, therefore order of b.p. is
$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathrm{CH}_{3} \mathrm{CH}_{2} \mathrm{CH}_{2} \mathrm{COOH}>\mathrm{CH}_{3} \mathrm{CH}_{2} \mathrm{CH}_{2} \mathrm{CH}_{2} \mathrm{OH} & \\
& >\mathrm{CH}_{3} \mathrm{CH}_{2} \mathrm{CH}_{2} \mathrm{CHO}
\end{aligned}
$$
